ted.  Timing and lack of server lag (and a low latency network connection) are obviously rather important here...  You can also see this happen with some AE effects (i.e. like when EVERYBODY fails vs. phara dar stun, regardless of resist stat, etc...).<br><br>So, why should you care?  Consider the possibilities...<br>If you see a cluster of crits during a fight, use a short but high damage offensive disc then.  Or choose then to cast a usually highly resisted debuff.  Or manaburn, with a significantly better chance for a crit... or chose then to pop /rampage on a 60mob AE pull. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Note, there's other times you might want to be observant as well... like when rolling /randoms, or doing tradeskill combines on expensive non-trivial items....<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucomparisonjones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Comparison Jones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will KICK YOUR @$$</span><br>  Posts: 454<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/20/02 1:34:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1693.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.nimueserver.com/images/personal/comp_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: An observation about the RNG...</span><hr size=1> Har har, me can jes sees it... <br><br>Comparison says, 'Ok buddy, yoo fight dat guard der, me hit da combine button whenever yoo gets a crit'<br> <p><center><img src=http://extremeannihilation.ni